{"questionId":"15265","questionHtml":"<p>Find the probability that at least one of the spins is yellow.</p>","markschemeHtml":"<p style=\"text-align:left;\"><span class=\"mjpage\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\"\\left( {\\frac{1}{2} \\times \\frac{1}{3}} \\right) + \\left( {\\frac{1}{6} \\times \\frac{1}{3}} \\right) + \\frac{1}{3}\">\n  <mrow>\n    <mo>(</mo>\n    <mrow>\n      <mfrac>\n        <mn>1</mn>\n        <mn>2</mn>\n      </mfrac>\n      <mo>×</mo>\n      <mfrac>\n        <mn>1</mn>\n        <mn>3</mn>\n      </mfrac>\n    </mrow>\n    <mo>)</mo>\n  </mrow>\n  <mo>+</mo>\n  <mrow>\n    <mo>(</mo>\n    <mrow>\n      <mfrac>\n        <mn>1</mn>\n        <mn>6</mn>\n      </mfrac>\n      <mo>×</mo>\n      <mfrac>\n        <mn>1</mn>\n        <mn>3</mn>\n      </mfrac>\n    </mrow>\n    <mo>)</mo>\n  </mrow>\n  <mo>+</mo>\n  <mfrac>\n    <mn>1</mn>\n    <mn>3</mn>\n  </mfrac>\n</math></span>&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;<em><strong>(M1)(M1)</strong></em></p>\n<p><strong>Note:</strong> Award <em><strong>(M1)</strong></em> for&nbsp;<span class=\"mjpage\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\"\\left( {\\frac{1}{2} \\times \\frac{1}{3}} \\right)\">\n  <mrow>\n    <mo>(</mo>\n    <mrow>\n      <mfrac>\n        <mn>1</mn>\n        <mn>2</mn>\n      </mfrac>\n      <mo>×</mo>\n      <mfrac>\n        <mn>1</mn>\n        <mn>3</mn>\n      </mfrac>\n    </mrow>\n    <mo>)</mo>\n  </mrow>\n</math></span> and&nbsp;<span class=\"mjpage\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\"\\left( {\\frac{1}{6} \\times \\frac{1}{3}} \\right)\">\n  <mrow>\n    <mo>(</mo>\n    <mrow>\n      <mfrac>\n        <mn>1</mn>\n        <mn>6</mn>\n      </mfrac>\n      <mo>×</mo>\n      <mfrac>\n        <mn>1</mn>\n        <mn>3</mn>\n      </mfrac>\n    </mrow>\n    <mo>)</mo>\n  </mrow>\n</math></span>&nbsp;or equivalent, and <em><strong>(M1)</strong></em> for&nbsp;<span class=\"mjpage\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\"\\frac{1}{3}\">\n  <mfrac>\n    <mn>1</mn>\n    <mn>3</mn>\n  </mfrac>\n</math></span> <strong>and&nbsp;</strong>adding only the three correct probabilities.</p>\n<p><strong>OR</strong></p>\n<p><span class=\"mjpage\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\"1 - {\\left( {\\frac{2}{3}} \\right)^2}\">\n  <mn>1</mn>\n  <mo>−</mo>\n  <mrow>\n    <msup>\n      <mrow>\n        <mo>(</mo>\n        <mrow>\n          <mfrac>\n            <mn>2</mn>\n            <mn>3</mn>\n          </mfrac>\n        </mrow>\n        <mo>)</mo>\n      </mrow>\n      <mn>2</mn>\n    </msup>\n  </mrow>\n</math></span>&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;<em><strong>(M1)(M1)</strong></em></p>\n<p><strong>Note:</strong>&nbsp;Award&nbsp;<em><strong>(M1)</strong></em>&nbsp;for&nbsp;<span class=\"mjpage\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\"{\\frac{2}{3}}\">\n  <mrow>\n    <mfrac>\n      <mn>2</mn>\n      <mn>3</mn>\n    </mfrac>\n  </mrow>\n</math></span> seen and&nbsp;<em><strong>(M1)</strong></em>&nbsp;for&nbsp;subtracting&nbsp;<span class=\"mjpage\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\"{\\left( {\\frac{2}{3}} \\right)^2}\">\n  <mrow>\n    <msup>\n      <mrow>\n        <mo>(</mo>\n        <mrow>\n          <mfrac>\n            <mn>2</mn>\n            <mn>3</mn>\n          </mfrac>\n        </mrow>\n        <mo>)</mo>\n      </mrow>\n      <mn>2</mn>\n    </msup>\n  </mrow>\n</math></span> from 1.&nbsp;This may be shown in a tree diagram with “yellow” and “not yellow” branches.</p>\n<p><span class=\"mjpage\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\"\\frac{5}{9}\">\n  <mfrac>\n    <mn>5</mn>\n    <mn>9</mn>\n  </mfrac>\n</math></span> (0.556, 0.555555…, 55.6%)&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;<em><strong>(A1)</strong></em><strong>(ft)</strong><em><strong>&nbsp; &nbsp;(C3)</strong></em></p>\n<p><strong>Note:&nbsp;</strong>Follow through marks may be awarded if their answer to part (a) is used in a correct calculation.</p>\n<p><em><strong>[3 marks]</strong></em></p>","meta":{"questionId":"15265","referenceCode":"19M.1.SL.TZ1.T_12b","subjectId":"50-dp-mathematics-analysis-and-approaches","title":"Find the probability that at least one of the spins is yellow.","paper":"1","level":"SL","questionNumber":"b","marksAvailable":"[Maximum mark: 3]","breadcrumbLabels":["Topic 4—Statistics and probability","Topic 5 —Calculus","Topic 5 —Calculus","SL 5.5—Integration introduction, areas between curve and x axis","Topic 4—Statistics and probability","SL 4.6—Combined, mutually exclusive, conditional, independence, prob diagrams"],"memberSectionIds":[],"sectionOrders":{}}}